<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n30161i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30161i">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30161i"> 161(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lethargy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The word &ldquo;<mark>lethargy</mark>&rdquo; has an interesting derivation, for it is derived from the Greek word &ldquo;Lethe&rdquo;, the river of forgetfulness of the Infernal Regions. In a lethargy one lies like a log in complete oblivion of all around. <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 40</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c13240j" href="c13all.htm#c13240j">VI.C.13:240(j)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
